    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-10-09T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-10-09T00:00:00-05:00" n="207"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d207">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 837.13/29.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        Chargé <persName type="to">Scholle</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-10-09">
                            <hi rend="italic">October 9, 1914</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: The Department has received your telegram of
                    October 4 concerning the status of the Cuban Amnesty Bill, in which you refer to
                    the Department’s recent telegraphic instructions.</p>
                <p>In reply the Department desires to say that it is glad to know that the President
                    of Cuba has given assurances that he will veto the Amnesty Bill.</p>
                <p>I am [etc.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Robert Lansing</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
